      "contents": "# Ingredients\r\n\r\n*   leg of lamb, deboned and trimmed (1.5kg net)\n\r\n*   3 red peppers, cut into quarters and seeds removed\n\r\n*   2 aubergines cut into 8 wedges lengthways.\n\r\n*   2 tbsp olive oil\n\r\n*   Salt and black pepper\n\n\r\n\r\n## Marinade\r\n\r\n*   6 garlic cloves, crushed\n\r\n*   Grated zest of 2 lemons\n\r\n*   100ml lemon juice\n\r\n*   A few sprigs of thyme leaves\n\r\n*   100ml olive oil\n\r\n*   1tsp salt\n\n\r\n\r\n## Sauce\r\n\r\n*   100ml olive oil\n\r\n*   175g whole almonds\n\r\n*   Grated zest of 1 lemon\n\r\n*   4 tbsp lemon juice\n\r\n*   2 tbsp honey\n\r\n*   2 tbsp orange flower water\n\r\n*   15g mint, finely chopped\n\r\n*   15g coriander leaves, finely chopped\n\n\r\n\r\n# Directions\r\n\r\n*   Start with the marinade. In a large bowl combine the garlic, lemon zest and juice, the picked thyme leaves, olive oil, 1\u00BD teaspoons of salt and 1 teaspoon of pepper and stir well.\n\r\n*   Divide the lamb into 4 or 5 even pieces and add to the marinade. Use your hands to massage the marinade into the meat. Put in the fridge and leave to marinate for a minimum of 2 hours or overnight.\n\r\n*   Preheat the oven to 220\u00BAC.\n\r\n*   Place a large ridged griddle pan on high heat. Toss the peppers in olive oil, salt and pepper and place on the grill. Cook until charred on all sides. Set aside to cool, then cut into 2 centimeter wide strips.\n\r\n*   Toss the aubergine wedges in olive oil, salt and pepper and place and the grill. Cook until charred on all sides. Set aside to cool.\n\r\n*   Put the lamb pieces on the hot grill and cook for 2-3 minutes on each side or until charred all over and starting to caramelise.\n\r\n*   Transfer the lamb, aubergines and peppers onto a roasting tray and put in the hot oven for 5-10 minutes. The meat should be rare to medium stage by then. Remove it from the oven, cover the tray with foil and leave to rest for 5-10 minutes.\n\r\n*   Meanwhile make the sauce. Heat 3 tablespoons of the olive oil in a small pan and add the almonds. Cook for 3-4 minutes stirring continuously until the nuts are golden brown and evenly cooked. Remove from the heat and allow to cool a little.\n\r\n*   Place the nuts in a food processor and roughly crush. Mix in the lemon zest and juice, honey, orange blossom water, \u00BD teaspoon of salt, \u00BD teaspoon of pepper and the remaining olive oil. Mix well and set aside.\n\r\n*   When you are ready to serve, carve the lamb into 1cm thick slices and arrange it on a platter along with the peppers and aubergines. Add the freshly chopped herbs to the sauce and spoon on top tossing it all together.\n\r\n*   This can be enough as it is, or you can server it with couscous.\n\n",
