      "id": 25,
      "title": "Courgette Moussaka",
      "description": "This started off as a way to use up excess allotment courgettes but it turned out extremely nice. It probably isn\u0027t authentically Greek in any way but it is very easy and very tasty. Of course, it would probably work just as well with aubergines. ",
      "contents": "# Ingredients\r\n\r\n*   1 kg of minced lamb\n\r\n*   2 onions\n\r\n*   4 cloves of garlic\n\r\n*   A bunch of chopped herbs (whatever is handy, e.g. oregano, mint, thyme, rosemary)\n\r\n*   Some tomato puree (a tbsp or 2)\n\r\n*   Some red wine (a glass or so)\n\r\n*   A couple of tbsp of ground spices made from toasted cumming seeds, toasted coriander seeds, cinnamon, nutmeg and black pepper\n\r\n*   Some fresh chilli finely chopped.\n\r\n*   Several courgettes, sliced lengthways\n\n\r\n\r\n# Ingredients for the topping\r\n\r\n*   250ml milk\n\r\n*   25 g butter\n\r\n*   25 g plain flour\n\r\n*   A couple of bay leave\n\r\n*   Some nutmeg\n\r\n*   A small handful of finely grated Parmesan cheese\n\r\n*   250g ricotta\n\r\n*   1 large egg\n\n",
