      "id": 26,
      "title": "Apple and walnut muffins",
      "description": "Muffins with apples , walnuts and cinnamon. ",
      "contents": "# Ingredients\r\n\r\n*   3 apples\n\r\n*   100 g walnuts\n\r\n*   175g plain flour\n\r\n*   150 g caster sugar\n\r\n*   1/2 tsp baking soda\n\r\n*   1tsp baking powder\n\r\n*   1/4 tsp salt\n\r\n*   2 eggs\n\r\n*   120ml vegetable oil\n\r\n*   1 tsp vanilla extract \n\r\n*   1 tsp cinnamon\n\n\r\n\r\n# Directions\r\n\r\n*   Toast the walnuts in a dry pan and roughly chop.\n\r\n*   Peel and dice the apples and mix with the cinnamon and walnuts.\n\r\n*   In a separate bowl mix the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.\n\r\n*   Whisk eggs and add oil and vanilla. \n\r\n*   Mix the apple mixture with the dry ingredients and fold in the eggs/oil mixture. \n\r\n*   Put the batter into 12 muffin tins \n\r\n*   Bake at 180C for about 25m. \n\n\r\n\r\nMakes about 12 muffins.\n",
