      "title": "Barbecued Pork Belly",
      "description": "Slow cooked pork belly with smoke",
      "contents": "# Ingredients\r\n\r\n*   \r\n\r\n One large piece of boned pork belly (at least 2kg\r\n\r\n A rub made with the following:\r\n\r\n*   Sugar - 3 parts\n\r\n*   Salt - 3 parts\n\r\n*   Gochugaru (Korean chilli powder) 3 part\n\r\n*   Garlic powder - 1 part\n\r\n*   Onion powder - 1 part\n\n\r\n\r\n## Directions\r\n\r\n*   Mix all ingredients for the rub\n\r\n*   Remove the skin from the pork and score the fat\n\r\n*   Apply rub and leave uncovered in the fridge overnight\n\r\n*   Smoke/BBQ for 5-6 hours at ~125C\n\r\n*   Remove, cover in foil and rest for about an hour\n\r\n*   Cut into thick slices for serving\n\n\n",
