      "title": "Dark Rye Loaf",
      "description": "Dark Scandinavian rye bread which is especially good with cured salmon. This needs to be started 4 days ahead and makes 2 large loaves.",
      "contents": "# Day 1\r\n\r\n## Ingredients\r\n\r\n*   2dl of natural yoghurt\n\r\n*   10g of dry yest\n\r\n*   1 tsp of salt\n\r\n*   100gr of rye flour\n\n\r\n\r\n## Directions\r\n\r\n*   Mix all ingredients, cover and leave in room temp for 2 days\n\n\r\n\r\n# Day 3\r\n\r\n## Ingredients\r\n\r\n*   300gr of sourdough from day1\n\r\n*   1l of water\n\r\n*   2 tbs salt\n\r\n*   350gr rye cross\n\r\n*   600gr of rye flour\n\n\r\n\r\n## Directions\r\n\r\n*   soften the dough in the water and mix in the other ingredients. Leave in room temp to the next day\n\n\r\n\r\n# Day 4\r\n\r\n## Ingredients\r\n\r\n*   33cl of dark beer\n\r\n*   2 tbs dark syrup\n\r\n*   125gr sunflower seeds\n\r\n*   125gr pumpkin seeds\n\r\n*   125gr flax seeds\n\r\n*   500gr rye flour\n\n\r\n\r\n## Directions\r\n\r\n*   Knock the dough back and mix in all ingredients. leave in room temp for 5 hr\n\r\n*   Grease two baking forms and cover with damp baking cloth. Leave for 2 hrs.\n\r\n*   Prick the dough with a fork and brush with oil\n\r\n*   Bake in 170-180C for 1hr45min. take out and leave in the forms for 30min before tipping out\n\n\n",
